51 inserted by section 6 of chapter 173 of the acts of 2022, or any other general or special law to the
52 contrary, the running race horse meeting licensee located in Suffolk county licensed to conduct
53 live racing pursuant to said chapter128A and simulcast wagering pursuant to said chapter 128C
54 in calendar year 2025 shall remain licensed as a running horse racing meeting licensee and shall
55 remain authorized to conduct simulcast wagering pursuant to said chapter 128C until December
56 15, 2027;provided, however, that the days between January 1, 2025 and December 31, 2027 shall
57 be dark days pursuant to said chapter 128C and the licensee shall be precluded from conducting
58 live racing during that period unless it applies for and is granted a supplemental live racing
59 license pursuant to said chapter 128A; provided further, that the licensee shall not simulcast or
60 accept a wager on greyhound dog racing on or after August 10, 2023 pursuant to section 9 of
61 chapter 128C of the General Laws; provided further, that all simulcasts shall comply with the
62 Interstate Horse Racing Act of 1978, 15 U.S.C. 3001et seq. or other applicable federal law;
63 provided further, that all simulcasts from states which have racing associations that do not
64 require approval in compliance with the Interstate Horse Racing Act of 1978, 15 U.S.C.
65 3004(a)(1)(A) shall require the approval of the New England Horsemen’s Benevolent &
66 Protective Association prior to being simulcast to a racing meeting licensee within the
67 commonwealth; and provided further, that if the association agrees to approve the simulcast for 1
68 racing meeting licensee, it shall approve the simulcast for all otherwise eligible racing meeting
69 licensees.
